</section>

<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <div class="ti">&#127885; BHGS #A49573</div>
    <div class="ti">&#128293; Gas &amp; Electric · Dual-Fuel</div>
    <div class="ti">&#9889; Same Day Service</div>
    <div class="ti">&#128203; Quote Before We Start</div>
    <div class="ti">&#128737; 90-Day Warranty</div>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>The most common range call &mdash; one burner won&rsquo;t light &mdash; is often a $160&ndash;$220 job</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Gas range ignition failures are the single most common range repair call in Los Angeles. A burner that clicks but won&rsquo;t light, or won&rsquo;t ignite after a boilover, is almost always an igniter or spark electrode issue &mdash; not a gas valve or control board problem. The repair is straightforward. Flat-rate pricing that assumes the worst-case component costs you more than you should pay.</p>
      <p>We diagnose first. The $89 fee covers the full diagnosis. Once we know which component failed &mdash; igniter, electrode, valve, element, board &mdash; we give you two numbers: labor and the specific OEM part. You approve before we start. A boilover that knocked out one burner igniter is a very different repair from a control board failure &mdash; and the price should reflect that.</p>
      <p>Gas range calls include supply pressure verification and a post-repair gas leak check at no extra charge. Any work involving gas components requires confirming safe operation before we leave. This is not an add-on fee &mdash; it&rsquo;s standard on every gas range call.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="type-grid">
      <div class="type-card">
        <h3>&#128293; Gas ranges</h3>
        <p>Surface igniters, spark electrodes, gas valves, safety valves. Most LA range calls are gas ignition. We confirm supply pressure and all burners before leaving.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <h3>&#9889; Electric ranges</h3>
        <p>Surface heating elements, infinite switches, control boards. Element failures are straightforward. Infinite switch failures cause uncontrolled heating &mdash; replace immediately.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <h3>&#128293;&#9889; Dual-fuel</h3>
        <p>Gas surface + electric oven. Wolf, Viking, Thermador, Bertazzoni. Both gas and electric systems in one unit. More complex to diagnose correctly &mdash; our techs know these configurations.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="transparency-block">
      <div class="tr-card them">
        <h3>Flat-Rate BlueBook pricing</h3>
        <ul class="tr-list">
          <li>Single price before diagnosis</li>
          <li>Labor and parts bundled</li>
          <li>One-burner repair priced like full replacement</li>
          <li>Gas safety check as add-on fee</li>
          <li>You don&rsquo;t know what the part costs</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="tr-card us">
        <h3>Our approach &mdash; labor + parts separate</h3>
        <ul class="tr-list">
          <li>Diagnose first, then quote</li>
          <li>One igniter vs. control board &mdash; different prices</li>
          <li>Gas pressure check and leak test included</li>
          <li>Boilover-related ignition often no part needed</li>
          <li>$89 diagnostic applied to the total</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

