            <td><div class="price-labor">$160&ndash;$300</div><div class="price-parts-note">+ igniter switch if needed</div></td>
            <td>Igniter switch failure or moisture in ignition module from boilover. Often resolves with drying. Switch replacement if failed.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="luxury-row">
            <td><div class="repair-type">Wolf / Viking / Thermador <span class="luxury-badge">LUXURY</span></div><div class="repair-desc">All failure types, gas, electric, dual-fuel</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$280&ndash;$680+</div><div class="price-parts-note">+ OEM parts (premium pricing)</div></td>
            <td>Proprietary high-BTU gas components, dual-fuel configurations, custom sealed burners, professional-grade control modules</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="luxury-row">
            <td><div class="repair-type">Bertazzoni / ILVE / Lacanche <span class="luxury-badge">LUXURY</span></div><div class="repair-desc">European professional ranges, all failure types</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$280&ndash;$640+</div><div class="price-parts-note">+ OEM parts (import lead times possible)</div></td>
            <td>Italian and European professional-grade ranges. Parts sometimes have 1&ndash;3 week lead times from European distribution. We advise on availability before confirming repair.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Diagnostic fee</div><div class="repair-desc">Service call + full diagnosis · gas includes pressure check</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$89</div><div class="price-parts-note">Applied to repair</div></td>
            <td>Applied to labor total when you approve the repair. Gas calls include supply pressure check and post-repair leak test.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="table-note"><strong>All prices are labor only.</strong> Parts quoted separately. Gas safety checks included on every gas range call. Quote before we start; invoice matches the quote. 90-day warranty on parts and labor.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Cost Factors</p>
    <h2>What affects range repair cost in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="factors-grid">
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128293;</div><h3>Gas vs. electric vs. dual-fuel</h3><p>Gas ignition is the most common failure and usually the least expensive. Electric ranges have simpler surface issues but more complex control boards. Dual-fuel configurations require knowledge of both systems &mdash; reflected in the higher luxury range labor.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128167;</div><h3>Boilover damage</h3><p>LA kitchens see a lot of boilover-caused ignition failures. Liquid in the ignition module shorts the spark circuit. This often resolves with drying at no parts cost. Flat-rate pricing assumes a part is needed before checking.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127991;</div><h3>Brand and configuration</h3><p>Standard brands (GE, Samsung, LG, Whirlpool) have widely available OEM igniters and elements. Wolf, Viking, Bertazzoni use proprietary gas components. European ranges may have import lead times &mdash; we advise upfront.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127959;</div><h3>Slide-in vs. freestanding</h3><p>Slide-in ranges sit flush with the counter and require more care to remove for access. Some repairs take longer on slide-ins &mdash; reflected in the quote before we start.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128293;</div><h3>Glass cooktop damage</h3><p>A cracked glass cooktop is a parts cost that can approach the value of the range itself. We quote the glass cost before recommending repair vs. replacement. Transparent in the separate parts quote.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128204;</div><h3>Root cause, not just symptom</h3><p>A burner that won&rsquo;t light might be a wet igniter, a failed electrode, or a bad spark module. We find which one before ordering parts. With separate labor and parts, you see exactly what the diagnosis found.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Repair vs. Replace</p>
    <h2>When to repair a range, when to replace it</h2>
    <p class="lead">We give you an honest assessment after diagnosis &mdash; the same one we&rsquo;d give if it were our own range.</p>
    <div class="rvr-grid">
      <div class="rvr-card repair">
        <h3>Repair makes sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Unit is under 12 years old</li>
          <li>Total repair (labor + parts) is under 50% of replacement</li>
          <li>Luxury range (Wolf, Viking, Bertazzoni) &mdash; these last 15&ndash;20 years</li>
          <li>Slide-in model in custom cabinetry &mdash; replacement is disruptive</li>
          <li>Single component failure (igniter, element, switch)</li>
          <li>Burner ignition issue &mdash; often very low total cost</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rvr-card replace">
        <h3>Replace makes more sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Budget range is 12&ndash;15+ years old</li>
          <li>Control board cost exceeds 60% of replacement value</li>
          <li>Glass cooktop crack where glass cost approaches range value</li>
          <li>Multiple components failing simultaneously</li>
          <li>Parts discontinued with no reliable ETA</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

