    <p class="sl">FAQ</p>
    <h2>Questions about range repair costs in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does range repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor typically runs $160&ndash;$400 for standard brands. Burner ignition issues &mdash; the most common call &mdash; run $160&ndash;$320 and often require no replacement part. Parts are quoted separately after diagnosis. Wolf and Viking luxury ranges run $280&ndash;$680+ in labor.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">One burner won&rsquo;t ignite. How much to fix?</div><div class="faq-a">A single gas burner not igniting is typically an igniter or spark electrode issue. Labor runs $160&ndash;$320 for standard brands. If a boilover caused it, the igniter module may just need drying &mdash; no parts cost. We check all burners while on site and confirm gas safety before leaving.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does Wolf or Viking range repair cost?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor for Wolf and Viking range repair runs $280&ndash;$680+ depending on the failure. These professional ranges use proprietary high-BTU gas components and dual-fuel configurations. OEM parts are premium-priced and quoted separately after diagnosis.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Why do you quote labor and parts separately?</div><div class="faq-a">Many LA repair companies use flat-rate BlueBook pricing. A boilover that just needs drying should not cost the same as replacing an ignition module. We quote separately so the price reflects your actual repair &mdash; and burner ignition calls are frequently much cheaper than people expect.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are parts included in the quoted labor price?</div><div class="faq-a">No &mdash; all prices on this page are labor only. After diagnosis we quote the specific part needed as a separate line item. Gas range calls include supply pressure verification and post-repair leak test at no extra charge. OEM parts used wherever available.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is the $89 diagnostic fee?</div><div class="faq-a">We charge $89 to come out and diagnose the problem. That fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work. If you decide not to repair, you pay $89 and we leave.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What warranty do you provide on range repair?</div><div class="faq-a">90 days on parts and labor. Same issue within 90 days &mdash; we come back at no charge. OEM parts wherever available.</div></div>
